text.section:
Upon submission of a proposed response action plan, the participant:
Shall publish a notice of a proposed response action plan once a week for 2 consecutive weeks in a daily or weekly newspaper of general circulation in the geographical area in which the eligible property is located that shall include:
A summary of the proposed response action plan;
The name and address of the participant and eligible property;
The name, address, and telephone number of the office within the Department from which information about the proposed response action plan may be obtained;
An address to which persons may submit written comments about the proposed response action plan;
A deadline for the close of the public comment period by which written comments must be received by the Department; and
The date and location of the public informational meeting; and
Shall post at the eligible property a notice of intent to conduct a response action plan at that property.
